   <concept id="FAR_13_501"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">13.501</ph> Special documentation requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d774e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d801e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						             Sole source (including brand name) acquisitions.</p>
               <ol id="d774e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d801e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 Acquisitions conducted under simplified acquisition procedures are exempt from the requirements in <xref href="Part_6.dita#FAR_Part_6"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>. However, contracting officers must-</p>
                     <ol id="d774e36" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e25" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
										                     Conduct sole source acquisitions, as defined in <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                                    base="i1125359"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>, (including brand name) under this subpart only if the need to do so is justified in writing and approved at the levels specified in paragraph (a)(2) of this section;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e33" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
										                     Prepare sole source (including brand name) justifications using the format at <xref href="6.303-2.dita#FAR_6_303_2"
                                    base="i1119771"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.303-2</xref>, modified to reflect that the procedures in FAR <xref href="Subpart_13.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_13_5"
                                    base="i1111258"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  13.5</xref> were used in accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.1901</xref> or the authority of <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.1903</xref>;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e50" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
										                     Make publicly available the justifications (excluding brand name) required by <xref href="6.305.dita#FAR_6_305"
                                    base="i1119843"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.305</xref>(a) within 14 days after contract award or in the case of unusual and compelling urgency within 30 days after contract award, in accordance with <xref href="6.305.dita#FAR_6_305"
                                    base="i1119843"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.305</xref> procedures at paragraphs (b), (d), (e), and (f); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e61" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph>
                              
										                     Make publicly available brand name justifications with the solicitation, in accordance with <xref href="5.102.dita#FAR_5_102"
                                    base="i1121037"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">5.102</xref>(a)(6).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d801e69" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                 Justifications and approvals are required under this subpart for sole-source (including brand-name) acquisitions or portions of an acquisition requiring a brand-name. If the justification is to cover only the portion of the acquisition which is brand-name, then it should so state; the approval level requirements will then only apply to that portion.</p>
                     <ol id="d774e108" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e75" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
										                     For a proposed contract exceeding the simplified acquisition threshold, but not exceeding 
											$750,000,
										 the contracting officer’s certification that the justification is accurate and complete to the best of the contracting officer’s knowledge and belief will serve as approval, unless a higher approval level is established in accordance with agency procedures.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e80" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
										                     For a proposed contract exceeding 
											$750,000
										 or the thresholds in paragraph (1) of the definition of simplified acquisition threshold in <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                                    base="i1125359"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>, but not exceeding $15 million, the advocate for competition for the procuring activity, designated pursuant to <xref href="6.501.dita#FAR_6_501"
                                    base="i1119317"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.501</xref>; or an official described in <xref href="6.304.dita#FAR_6_304"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(3) or (a)(4) must approve the justification and approval. This authority is not delegable.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e94" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
										                     For a proposed contract exceeding 
											$15 million
										 but not exceeding $75 million or, for DoD, NASA, and the Coast Guard, not exceeding $100 million, the head of the procuring activity or the official described in <xref href="6.304.dita#FAR_6_304"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(3) or (a)(4) must approve the justification and approval. This authority is not delegable.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d801e102" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph>
                              
										                     For a proposed contract exceeding 
											$75 million
										 or, for DoD, NASA, and the Coast Guard, $100 million, the official described in <xref href="6.304.dita#FAR_6_304"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(4) must approve the justification and approval. This authority is not delegable except as provided in <xref href="6.304.dita#FAR_6_304"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(4).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d801e113" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contract file documentation.</i> The contract file must include-</p>
               <ol id="d774e176" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d801e121" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 A brief written description of the procedures used in awarding the contract, including the fact that the procedures in FAR <xref href="Subpart_13.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_13_5"
                              base="i1111258"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  13.5</xref> were used;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d801e129" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                 The number of offers received;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d801e134" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
								                 An explanation, tailored to the size and complexity of the acquisition, of the basis for the contract award decision; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d801e139" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
								                 Any justification approved under paragraph (a) of this section.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
